x4freetext: The pulsed beam consisted of 1 ns long
bursts separated by 106 ns.
A large area 357 mm x 284 mm position sensitive
multiwire proportional counter covering laboratory
angles from 95-170 degree. The detector`s position
response function was determined  by Rutherford
scattering of 31P beams off 197Au targets at beam
energies well below the fusion barrier.
178Hf targets consisted of 200 mg/cm2 of metal
evaporated onto 30 mg/cm2 backing foils of aluminum.
No information on the sample composition.
Time-of-flight measurements of fission fragments
The measured fission fragment angular
distributions was converted to the center of mass
frame using fission total kinetic energies from
systematics and fitted in the zero-spin limit to
determine fission cross sections and anisotropies.
Table II of Phys.Rev.C 66(2002)044601

x4freetext: The pulsed beam consisted of 1 ns long
bursts separated by 106 ns.
A large area 357 mm x 284 mm position sensitive
multiwire proportional counter covering laboratory
angles from 95-170 degree. The detector`s position
response function was determined  by Rutherford
scattering of 31P beams off 197Au targets at beam
energies well below the fusion barrier.
Lutetium oxide reduced to metal
using thorium, and then sputtered onto a carbon
backing. Target thickness 20 - 40 ug/cm2.
Thorium concentration 22-28%.
The measured fission fragment angular
distributions was converted to the center of mass
frame using fission total kinetic energies from
systematics and fitted in the zero-spin limit to
determine fission cross sections and anisotropies.
Data were corrected for the 175Lu and 232Th fission
contribution.
Table V. of Phys.Rev.C 66(2002)044601
